# How to Navigate and Maintain These Docs

## The hierarchy
- **CLAUDE.md** — always loaded (≤200 lines); entry point and pointer map
- **CLAUDE.local.md** — personal preferences; add to .gitignore (≤200 lines)
- **docs/OVERVIEW.md** — architecture and data flow; loaded on demand (≤400 lines)
- **docs/{component}.md** — deep dives per component; loaded on demand (≤300 lines)
- **.claude/rules/** — domain conventions; auto-loaded when editing matched files (≤100 lines each)
- **~/.claude/rules/** — your personal rules; loaded for all projects (≤100 lines each)
- **.claude/context-map.md** — lookup index: "to find X, read Y" (≤150 lines)
- **Auto memory (MEMORY.md)** — Claude-managed session learnings; not generated by this tool

## Subagent Context

When Claude spawns a subagent:
- The subagent gets its own copy of CLAUDE.md (same file, separate context)
- Path-scoped rules (.claude/rules/) load for subagents too when they edit matching files
- Auto memory from the main session is NOT loaded in the subagent
- Component docs linked from this system are designed to be self-contained —
  a subagent reading just `docs/api.md` should have everything it needs

## When to update

- New component added → create `docs/{component}.md`, add pointer in CLAUDE.md navigation table
- API changes → update `.claude/rules/api.md` + relevant component doc
- Repo-wide convention changes → update CLAUDE.md
- Build/test commands change → update CLAUDE.md and auto memory will learn the rest
- Large drift from reality → run: `/agentify update`

## Token budgets

| File | Limit |
|------|-------|
| CLAUDE.md | ≤200 lines |
| CLAUDE.local.md | ≤200 lines |
| .claude/rules/*.md | ≤100 lines each |
| ~/.claude/rules/*.md | ≤100 lines each |
| docs/OVERVIEW.md | ≤400 lines |
| docs/{component}.md | ≤300 lines each |
| .claude/context-map.md | ≤150 lines |
| docs/plans/README.md | ≤80 lines |
| docs/specs/README.md | ≤80 lines |
| docs/reviews/README.md | ≤80 lines |

Overflow always moves **down** the hierarchy, never up.

## Agent Coordination Directories (optional)

Created by agentify when multi-agent signals are detected or explicitly requested.

- **docs/plans/** — implementation plans for agents to pick up and execute.
  Each file is one plan: goal, context, acceptance criteria, steps.
- **docs/specs/** — feature/API/component specifications agents work from.
  Each file is one spec: requirements, interface, constraints, examples.
- **docs/reviews/** — code and design review findings. Each file is one
  review: scope, findings by severity, decisions made.

agentify owns only the `README.md` stubs in these directories. All other
files (`*.md` excluding README) are agent work artifacts and are never
overwritten by agentify.
